<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>8 SPEED, 9 SPEED, AND 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - AIR SYSTEM - RANGE VALVE A-3546</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>RANGE VALVE A-3546</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301807">Figure 7</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301807" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301807" filename="../figg13/G1301807.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Range Valve A-3546 Exploded View</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal and Disassembly</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the air lines and loosen the clamp securing the valve to gear shift lever.
                    Remove the valve.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the four screws to separate the front and rear housings and remove the slide and
                    two sets of position springs and balls.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the seal, insert valve O-ring and spring from rear housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If necessary, remove the two felt seals. Punch out the roll pin to remove the control
                    knob from the slide.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Reassembly and Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301807">Figure 7</hotlnk>
                    for proper reassembly. Use a VERY SMALL amount of silicone lubricant on the O-rings to avoid
                    clogging ports. A small amount of grease on the position springs and balls will help to hold them in
                    place during reassembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the air lines with their sheathing and O-rings on the gear shift lever.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure the valve on the gear shift lever with mounting clamp. The control knob should
                    face to the front and be approximately 6 inches below the centerline of the ball grip.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach the air lines.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
